The '''[[GNU]] Image Manipulation Program''' ('''GIMP''') is a [[free software]] [[raster graphics editor]]. The GIMP product vision sees GIMP as a high end program for the editing and creation of Original Images, icons, graphical elements of web pages and art for user interface elements. The product vision also sees GIMP as a platform for the development of cutting edge scientific image processing algorithms <ref>[http://gui.gimp.org/index.php/GIMP_UI_Redesign GIMP UI Redesign - Product Vision]</ref>.
The aims laid out by the GIMP product vision varies a lot from the beginings of GIMP as a university project started in 1995 by [[Peter Mattis]] and [[Spencer Kimball]], currently GIMP is maintained and enhanced by a group of volunteers under the auspices of the [[GNOME|GNOME Project]]<ref>{{cite web | title = GNOME: The free software desktop project | url = http://www.gnome.org}}</ref>.
